.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBconnect(This :: wxEvtHandler(),\fR
\fB              EventType :: wxEventType(),\fR
\fB              [Option]) ->\fR
\fB                 ok\fR
\fB                 when\fR
\fB                     Option ::\fR
\fB                         {id, integer()} |\fR
\fB                         {lastId, integer()} |\fR
\fB                         {skip, boolean()} |\fR
\fB                         callback |\fR
\fB                         {callback, function()} |\fR
\fB                         {userData, term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
This function subscribes to events.

.PP
Subscribes to events of type \fIEventType\fR, in the range \fIid\fR, \fIlastId\fR.

.PP
The events will be received as messages if no callback is supplied.

.PP
Options

.PP
id:\fI{id, integer()} \fRThe identifier (or first of the identifier range) to be associated with this event handler. Default is ?wxID_ANY

.PP
lastid:\fI{lastId,integer()} \fRThe second part of the identifier range. If used 'id' must be set as the starting identifier range. Default is ?wxID_ANY

.PP
skip:\fI{skip,boolean()} \fRIf skip is true further event_handlers will be called. This is not used if the 'callback' option is used. Default is \fIfalse\fR.

.PP
callback:\fI{callback,function()} \fRUse a callback\fIfun(EventRecord::wx(),EventObject::wxObject()) \fRto process the event. Default not specified i.e. a message will be delivered to the process calling this function.

.PP
userData:\fI{userData,term()} \fRAn erlang term that will be sent with the event. Default: [].


.RE
.B
\fBdisconnect(This :: wxEvtHandler(),\fR
\fB                 EventType :: wxEventType(),\fR
\fB                 [Option]) ->\fR
\fB                    boolean()\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        Option ::\fR
\fB                            {id, integer()} |\fR
\fB                            {lastId, integer()} |\fR
\fB                            {callback, function()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
This function unsubscribes the process or callback fun from the event handler.

.PP
EventType may be the atom 'null' to match any eventtype. Notice that the options skip and userdata is not used to match the eventhandler.


.RE
